 \sum_{n = 0}^{10} \frac {1 + (-1)^n} {2^n} 
n^2
n^3
 \begin{align}\sum_{n=0}^{10}\frac{1+(-1)^n}{2^n}&=\frac{1+(-1)^0}{2^0}+\frac{1+(-1)^1}{2^1}+\frac{1+(-1)^2}{2^2}+\ldots +\frac{1+(-1)^{10}}{2^{10}}\\ &=\frac21+0+\frac24+0+\frac2{16}+0+\frac2{64}+0+\frac2{256}+0+\frac2{1024}\\ &=\frac{1024+256+64+16+4+1}{512}=\frac{1365}{512}\end{align}
